  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/248",
  "title": "Communication between widget?",
  "body": "Hello I have a problem with our current widget API. I want to be able to generate a url in the RefinementList but anything related to URL's are in the dedicated widget. And because we have some configuration in the urlSync that will make the configuration look different, we need the RefinementList widget to be able to get infos about url generation.\n\nSeveral options I have had in mind so far : \n- pass the UrlSync widget manually / by the user, directly to the other widget factory (explicit and straightforward but let the user do stuff)\n- let the urlSync widget export a function with a name/key, and let the others access it using the key/name... Could look a bit like runtime dependency injection. (smell the magic yet ? ;) )\n\nDo you have something else in mind? Better/nicer/less magic/less like a fat framework :P\n",
